<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="skill-n">skill <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /skɪl/    美 /skɪl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>技巧；技艺</strong></h4>
<p>the ability to do sth well:</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He played the piano <strong>with skill</strong>.
他钢琴弹得很娴熟。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He has great <strong>skill in / at</strong> drawing.
他画画很有技巧。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>技能</strong></h4>
<p>an ability that you need to do a job, etc. well：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Remembering names is an important social skill.
记住人名是一种重要的社交技能。</p><footer>2009 安徽</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Reading skills include skipping, skimming, scanning, and so on. 
阅读技巧包括跳读、略读、查读等。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mastery of a skill is much better than storing up a thousand pieces of gold. 
一艺在身，胜积千金。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>skilled /skɪld/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>skilled craftsmen 
技术熟练的工匠</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Dad was quite <strong>skilled in / at</strong> sailing, but not good at swimming.
爸爸擅长驾船航行，但不擅长游泳。</p><footer>2011 重庆</footer></div></div>